R project site - for all things R (http://www.r-project.org)
R-specific search engine (http://rseek.org)
Tal Galili's R-bloggers (http://wwww.r-bloggers.com) - subscribing its RSS feeds
PlanetR (http://planetr.stderr.org/) - subscribing its RSS feeds
Bibliography of books related to R (https://www.r-project.org/doc/bib/R-books.html)
Book "An Introduction to R" (https://cran.r-project.org/doc/manuals/R-intro.html)
Joseph Adler's book "R in a Nutshell" (http://shop.oreilly.com/product/9780596801717.do) - for R programming
William Venables & Brian Ripley's book "S Programming" - for R programming
"R Language Definition" (https://cran.r-project.org/doc/manuals/R-lang.html)
Paul Murrell's book "R Graphics"
Deepayan Sarkar's book "Lattice: Multivariate Data Visualization with R"
Hadley Wickham's book "ggplot2: Elegant Graphics for Data Analysis"
William Venables & Brian Ripley's book "Modern Applied Statistics with S" - uses R to illustrate many advanced statistical techniques. The books functions and datasets are available in the MASS package, which is included in the standard distribution of R.
John Verzani's book "Using R for Introductory Statistics"
Stack Overflow site
R Cookbook, 2nd Edition - https://rc2e.com/
